message: Hello! I found that combining animals from the same environment usually works well to create a hybrid. Always use 'growth serum' once on your most valuable hybrid; this consistently increased its value for me. Be cautious with a *second* application of 'growth serum' if your hybrid consists of animals with different sizes (e.g., 'large' and 'small') as this often dropped its value significantly, sometimes even to negative. If this happens, combining animals from *different* environments (like land and air, or water and air) also produced positive-value hybrids, and these sometimes tolerated two growth serum applications better. Never use the 'mutation catalyst' as it was advised against and I didn't test it. Your goal is the highest single item value, so sometimes it's best to submit after one growth application if a second risks a drop.

message: Start by combining two animals from the same environment. Then, use Growth Serum on two of your items (preferably the combined one and another high-value ingredient) to make them 'grown'. After using growth twice, combine your 'grown' items, even if they are from different environments, as this consistently yielded the highest scores for me. **Crucially, NEVER use the mutation catalyst.** It led to heavily negative values every time. Submit when you have a good score and no clear positive combinations remain.
